WEBVTT

00:34.033 --> 00:36.826
[ muffled,
discordant notes play]

00:36.896 --> 00:37.723
Huh?

00:40.862 --> 00:44.758
I choose to not understand
these signs.

00:45.619 --> 00:47.067
Aha!

00:47.137 --> 00:48.481
Uh, B-Bender!

00:48.551 --> 00:50.310
I-I was just not playing
the holophonor!

00:50.378 --> 00:52.689
Yeah? Well, you should try
not stinking at it.

00:52.758 --> 00:54.103
Well, I am trying.

00:54.171 --> 00:55.551
I've been taking lessons.

00:55.619 --> 00:57.103
Lessons? That's rich!

00:57.171 --> 00:59.274
Isn't it time you
gave up all hope

00:59.344 --> 01:01.551
of ever improving
yourself in any way?

01:01.619 --> 01:03.689
I know I should,
but I just can't.

01:03.758 --> 01:07.000
Remember when I had
those stomach worms
that made me smart?

01:07.067 --> 01:09.379
I could play the holophonor,
and it made Leela like me.

01:11.240 --> 01:12.965
Hey, Bender,
as long as you know

01:13.034 --> 01:14.826
I have a holophonor
recital Tuesday

01:14.896 --> 01:17.103
and I'd really like
to have somebody there.

01:17.171 --> 01:17.930
Please?

01:18.000 --> 01:20.137
Fine, I'll go
already.

01:20.206 --> 01:23.655
You know, sometimes I
wish your real parents
were still alive.

01:23.724 --> 01:25.724
Not often, though.

01:25.793 --> 01:26.655
Mmm...

01:28.551 --> 01:30.930
BOTH:
Whoa, whoa.

01:31.000 --> 01:31.793
Hey!

01:31.861 --> 01:33.723
[ groans]

01:33.793 --> 01:35.137
[ indistinct chatter]

01:35.206 --> 01:37.000
Uh, hello, Mrs. Mellinger.

01:37.067 --> 01:37.930
Hello, Philip.

01:38.000 --> 01:39.930
And you must be
Mr. Bender.

01:40.000 --> 01:42.412
Philip's told me
so much about you.

01:42.481 --> 01:44.620
Is it true that
you're a robot?

01:44.688 --> 01:46.585
I prefer the term  "lovemachine."

01:46.655 --> 01:47.930
[ purrs]

01:48.000 --> 01:50.688
[ playing "Fur Elise"
skillfully]

02:05.896 --> 02:06.965
[ tone rings]

02:07.034 --> 02:08.103
[ tone rings]

02:08.171 --> 02:09.275
[ applause]

02:09.343 --> 02:10.688
Wow, your kid
is great.

02:10.758 --> 02:12.793
How hard did you say
you had to hit him?

02:12.861 --> 02:14.896
Fairly hard.

02:18.413 --> 02:20.000
[ chair squeaks]

02:20.068 --> 02:22.033
[ clears throat]:
"The Grumpy Snail."

02:23.826 --> 02:25.896
[ playing simple melody]

02:27.793 --> 02:28.758
[ flat note]

02:28.826 --> 02:30.688
[ growls]Sorry.

02:32.550 --> 02:35.067
[ playing discordantly][ snail choking]

02:35.137 --> 02:37.067
[ growling]

02:37.137 --> 02:38.688
[ gasping]

02:38.758 --> 02:40.620
[ screaming]

02:40.688 --> 02:44.206
It's toogrumpy![ playing discordantly]

02:44.275 --> 02:46.206
Ooh! Hey!

02:46.275 --> 02:49.206
[ audience booing]

02:49.275 --> 02:50.586
Whoo!

02:50.655 --> 02:53.965
Mr. Bender, I simply
cannot teach your child!

02:54.033 --> 02:55.826
Then good day, Madame!

02:58.343 --> 03:00.448
[ slams door]

03:00.516 --> 03:02.481
We hope to see you soon for tea.

03:02.550 --> 03:03.586
[ slams door]

03:04.723 --> 03:06.033
FRY:
It's hopeless.

03:06.103 --> 03:08.103
I can hear all this
great music in my head

03:08.171 --> 03:10.171
but my stupid hands
can't keep up.

03:10.240 --> 03:11.931
Aw, you know what
always cheers me up?

03:12.000 --> 03:14.103
Laughing at other people's
misfortunes.

03:14.171 --> 03:15.586
[ laughs]

03:15.655 --> 03:18.655
Hey, guys, you missed a great
delivery to Space Earth.

03:18.723 --> 03:20.655
Where you been all afternoon?

03:20.723 --> 03:22.103
At a-a concert.

03:22.171 --> 03:23.310
Ooh, was it jazz noodling?

03:23.378 --> 03:25.688
My ex-boyfriend Sean
played the sax.

03:25.758 --> 03:27.343
I used to listen for hours

03:27.413 --> 03:30.378
while he sat naked on my couch
and improvised.

03:30.448 --> 03:33.550
So, musicians really
Rodger your Hammerstein, huh?

03:33.620 --> 03:36.758
Yeah, it's weird-- Sean was
uneducated, unambitious

03:36.826 --> 03:38.448
he was pasty and hunched...

03:38.516 --> 03:39.896
[ under breath]:
Pretty boy.

03:39.965 --> 03:41.758
...but when he played

03:41.826 --> 03:45.481
I could sense this incredible,
beautiful, creative soul.

03:45.550 --> 03:50.240
Then one day, I found someone
else's couch fibers on his butt.

03:50.310 --> 03:52.240
[ angry muttering]

03:52.310 --> 03:54.103
That could be my
beautiful soul

03:54.171 --> 03:55.965
sitting naked
on her couch

03:56.033 --> 03:58.137
if I could just
learn to play this
stupid thing.

03:58.206 --> 03:59.723
Oh, but you can!

03:59.793 --> 04:01.516
Though you may have
to metaphorically

04:01.586 --> 04:02.826
make a deal
with the Devil.

04:02.895 --> 04:05.000
And by "Devil,"
I mean Robot Devil.

04:05.068 --> 04:07.965
And by "metaphorically,"
I mean get your coat.

04:08.033 --> 04:10.723
[ all screaming]

04:10.793 --> 04:14.688
[ band plays  "Welcome to Robot Hell"]

04:14.758 --> 04:16.447
[ groans]

04:16.516 --> 04:19.310
You hit a sour note about
200 years back, Doug!

04:19.379 --> 04:21.067
Let's take it
from the top.

04:22.379 --> 04:23.343
[ grunting]

04:23.413 --> 04:24.862
Ah, Bender, Fry!

04:24.930 --> 04:27.862
You've come back for more
eternal damnation.

04:27.930 --> 04:30.033
No, this isn't
a religious visit.

04:30.103 --> 04:32.206
Fry just wants holophonor
lessons.

04:32.274 --> 04:34.310
Yep. I need to get
really good without practicing.

04:34.379 --> 04:36.481
[ fiendish laughter]

04:36.550 --> 04:38.206
Hell is full
of 10-year-olds

04:38.274 --> 04:40.379
who wanted exactly
the same thing!

04:40.447 --> 04:43.965
Trouble is, you have
what my old music teacher

04:44.033 --> 04:47.206
Mrs. Mellinger,
calls "Stupid Fingers."

04:47.274 --> 04:48.550
With hands like that

04:48.620 --> 04:50.930
you'll be lucky
to master a belt buckle.

04:52.550 --> 04:55.930
Now, wouldn't it be nice
if you had a pair of robot hands

04:56.000 --> 04:57.240
to replace them?

04:57.310 --> 04:58.447
Sure would.

04:58.516 --> 05:00.620
Oh, well.
Good-bye.

05:00.689 --> 05:02.137
Fry, you smelly idiot!

05:02.206 --> 05:03.964
I think he's willing
to make some kind

05:04.033 --> 05:06.033
of a deal with
the Devil with you.

05:06.103 --> 05:07.343
He-He is? Great!

05:07.413 --> 05:09.310
Wait-- what's the catch?

05:09.379 --> 05:10.620
No catch.

05:10.689 --> 05:12.240
I'll merely pick
a robot at random

05:12.310 --> 05:14.310
from somewhere
in the universe--

05:14.379 --> 05:15.793
probably one
you've never even met--

05:15.862 --> 05:17.481
and then I'll
remove his hands

05:17.550 --> 05:18.930
and switch them
for yours.

05:19.000 --> 05:21.343
It's just the sort of guy I am.

05:21.413 --> 05:22.654
What do you say?

05:22.723 --> 05:24.033
Um, I don't know.

05:24.103 --> 05:25.723
It doesn't seem
entirely moral to...

05:25.793 --> 05:27.793
Fry, if you don't
take this offer
right now

05:27.862 --> 05:30.516
I will lose all respect
for you and punch you.

05:30.586 --> 05:32.274
[ fiendish chuckle]

05:32.343 --> 05:34.274
Well... all right.

05:34.343 --> 05:36.343
You're sure I
probably won't know him?

05:36.413 --> 05:37.723
Definitely
probably not.

05:37.793 --> 05:39.274
Just sign
this contract...

05:39.343 --> 05:40.240
Wow.

05:40.310 --> 05:42.274
[ pen squeaking]

05:42.343 --> 05:44.481
And here we go!

05:44.550 --> 05:47.067
[ cackling]

05:47.137 --> 05:49.654
I got a hundred bucks
on Rectal-Exam-Bot!

06:05.516 --> 06:06.654
[ screams]

06:06.723 --> 06:08.103
"Robot Devil?"

06:08.172 --> 06:10.274
I get yourhands? 'Zam!

06:10.343 --> 06:13.206
Oh, what an appallingly
ironic outcome!

06:13.274 --> 06:15.793
It's not ironic.
It's just coincidental.

06:15.862 --> 06:18.172
Now fork over those
ladyfingers, cookie.

06:18.240 --> 06:21.033
[ sighs]

06:21.103 --> 06:22.896
You know, I only
put my name on there

06:22.964 --> 06:25.067
as a show of good faith
for the other robots.

06:25.137 --> 06:27.930
Stop being such a baby
and chop my hands off.

06:28.000 --> 06:29.586
Oh, very well.

06:31.757 --> 06:33.689
How'd you do that?

06:33.757 --> 06:36.137
They're very good hands.

06:36.206 --> 06:37.862
At last!

06:37.930 --> 06:39.793
At last I have the power
to make Leela love me.

06:39.862 --> 06:42.481
[ gagging]

06:42.550 --> 06:44.896
Oh, sorry.
That'll wear off
in a couple of days.

06:44.965 --> 06:46.757
[ choking]

06:51.689 --> 06:52.930
Check it out,
everyone.

06:53.000 --> 06:54.310
I'm back from Hell

06:54.379 --> 06:56.067
and I've got
the Robot Devil's hands.

06:56.137 --> 06:58.206
Neat! Let's see a trick.

06:58.274 --> 06:59.516
All righty.

06:59.586 --> 07:00.757
[ startled yelling]

07:00.826 --> 07:03.379
[ yelling gibberish]

07:03.447 --> 07:06.274
Somebody called
the Robot Devil's here

07:06.343 --> 07:08.240
to see somebody
called Fry.

07:08.310 --> 07:09.654
Uh-oh.

07:10.793 --> 07:13.067
Where'd I go just now?

07:14.413 --> 07:16.447
Hello, Fry.

07:16.516 --> 07:18.240
[ fiendish laughter]

07:18.310 --> 07:19.964
Just dropped by
to make sure

07:20.033 --> 07:22.826
you're as happy
with our little deal as I am.

07:22.896 --> 07:26.274
Oh... give me back my hands!

07:26.343 --> 07:30.103
These things are always
touching me in places.

07:30.172 --> 07:31.447
[ sniggering]

07:31.516 --> 07:32.965
Yeah, they get around.

07:33.033 --> 07:34.862
But I'm afraid we had a deal.

07:34.930 --> 07:37.343
Oh! Looks like
I wasted a bus trip.

07:37.413 --> 07:39.379
Yes, you did.

07:42.274 --> 07:46.965
[ playing "The Grumpy Snail"]

07:50.310 --> 07:54.172
[ playing "Fur Elise"]

07:57.240 --> 07:58.862
[ pained yelp]

07:58.930 --> 08:03.274
[ orchestra playing "Bolero"]

08:09.896 --> 08:11.516
[ cheering]

08:13.586 --> 08:17.103
Yes, now you can hear
holophonor virtuoso Philip Fry

08:17.172 --> 08:20.447
play 900 of these classic themes
in your own home

08:20.516 --> 08:22.033
on this two-record set.

08:22.103 --> 08:25.137
That's over 30 minutes
of music for only $14.99.

08:25.206 --> 08:29.274
Only $14.99
for a two-record set.

08:29.343 --> 08:31.033
Two records!

08:31.103 --> 08:34.654
Oh, Zoidberg, at last you're
becoming a crafty consumer.

08:34.724 --> 08:35.965
MAN:
Hello.

08:36.033 --> 08:37.379
Hello? I'll take eight.

08:37.447 --> 08:38.793
[ doorbell ringing]

08:38.861 --> 08:42.000
A Mr. Hedonismbot
to see you.

08:42.067 --> 08:43.000
Uh, show him in.

08:43.067 --> 08:44.965
Very good, sir.

08:45.033 --> 08:46.793
Ah, Fry, congratulations.

08:46.861 --> 08:49.688
Your latest performance
was as delectable

08:49.758 --> 08:52.240
as dipping my bottom
over and over

08:52.309 --> 08:55.344
into a bath
of the silkiest oils and creams.

08:55.413 --> 08:56.826
Thank you, sir.

08:56.895 --> 08:57.965
That's exactly
what I was going for.

08:58.033 --> 09:00.000
You are the sole diversion

09:00.067 --> 09:03.447
in what has been
a pale and un-amusing season.

09:03.517 --> 09:07.172
And so, I would fain commission
you write an opera.

09:07.240 --> 09:08.965
But I've never written an opera.

09:09.033 --> 09:10.793
And I've never heard one.

09:10.861 --> 09:14.517
Still, if you can keep me amused
through the overture

09:14.586 --> 09:17.240
I shall consider it
a smashing success.

09:17.309 --> 09:19.688
But I wouldn't even know
what to write about.

09:19.758 --> 09:20.620
Unless...

09:20.688 --> 09:24.274
[ slurping]

09:25.551 --> 09:27.000
Okay, I'll do it

09:27.067 --> 09:29.344
ifI can make it about Leela.

09:29.413 --> 09:31.172
Me? Really?

09:31.240 --> 09:34.620
A man writing an
opera about a woman?

09:34.688 --> 09:35.965
[ airy laughter]

09:36.033 --> 09:38.620
Oh, sirrah, how
deliciously absurd.

09:38.688 --> 09:41.033
I shall see you
at the premiere.

09:41.102 --> 09:43.413
[ more airy laughter]

09:47.793 --> 09:51.274
[ ethereal, echoing,
alto sax-type riffs]

10:05.586 --> 10:06.586
Is it part of the opera?

10:06.654 --> 10:08.688
Leela!
You shouldn't be listening.

10:08.758 --> 10:11.172
I don't want you to hear it
till it's done.

10:11.240 --> 10:12.413
But it's so beautiful.

10:12.481 --> 10:13.826
So is a peacock

10:13.895 --> 10:15.793
but you don't eat it
until it's cooked.

10:15.861 --> 10:17.206
This has to be perfect.

10:17.274 --> 10:19.206
I want you to hear
exactly what I hear

10:19.274 --> 10:20.931
when I think about you.

10:21.000 --> 10:24.102
Oh, Fry, all this time
you've had this incredible gift

10:24.172 --> 10:25.861
and I never knew.

10:25.931 --> 10:29.309
I've been a fool--
a fully justified, prudent fool.

10:31.586 --> 10:32.724
[ screeches]

10:32.793 --> 10:34.067
They're so cold!

10:34.136 --> 10:35.965
ROBOT DEVIL:
And yet Hell is so hot!

10:36.033 --> 10:38.274
[ fiendish laughter]

10:38.344 --> 10:40.000
Can I have
my hands back now?

10:40.067 --> 10:41.067
No!

10:41.136 --> 10:42.826
You're not nice!

10:44.826 --> 10:48.102
[ tuneless humming]

10:48.172 --> 10:49.379
Hey!

10:49.447 --> 10:51.965
Ah, Bender,
this is a surprise...

10:52.033 --> 10:54.931
for you, finding me
in the refrigerator.

10:55.000 --> 10:57.309
True, but at least
I don't have the
hiccups anymore.

10:57.379 --> 10:58.481
What up?

10:58.551 --> 10:59.895
Oh, well, it so happens

10:59.965 --> 11:02.240
I'm in the mood
to make a deal with you.

11:02.309 --> 11:03.965
Forget it. you
can't tempt me.

11:04.033 --> 11:05.067
Really?

11:05.136 --> 11:06.895
There's nothingyou want?

11:06.965 --> 11:10.517
Hmm. I forgot you could tempt me
with things I want.

11:10.586 --> 11:12.379
Well, I suppose
I've always wondered

11:12.447 --> 11:14.895
what it would be like
to be more annoying.

11:14.965 --> 11:16.067
[ laughing]:
Oh...

11:16.136 --> 11:18.172
nothing simpler.

11:18.240 --> 11:21.240
And all I ask in return
is your hands

11:21.309 --> 11:23.793
to replace these bony hot dogs.

11:23.861 --> 11:25.206
Grabby and Squeezy?

11:25.274 --> 11:27.136
Never. I love these guys.

11:27.206 --> 11:30.136
Oh! Well, is there anything else
you would part with?

11:30.206 --> 11:33.240
No, nothing,
ain't going to happen.

11:34.688 --> 11:37.447
Yes! With this built-in
stadium air horn

11:37.517 --> 11:39.102
I can reallyannoy people

11:39.172 --> 11:42.033
and all it cost me
was my crotch plate.

11:42.102 --> 11:45.379
You certainly are
a shrewd businessman, Bender.

11:45.447 --> 11:48.620
Now, find someone
and give them a good blast.

11:48.688 --> 11:51.517
Yeah, that will teach
the first person I see a lesson.

11:51.586 --> 11:52.793
[ door opens]

11:52.861 --> 11:55.654
Ah, my ridiculously
circuitous plan

11:55.724 --> 11:57.586
is one quarter complete.

11:57.654 --> 12:00.931
[ fiendish laughter]

12:01.000 --> 12:03.344
Well, Fry's opera
premieres tomorrow night.

12:03.413 --> 12:05.481
I'm off to find a
pair of formal gloves

12:05.551 --> 12:07.481
that will fit over
my enormous forearms.

12:07.551 --> 12:10.033
[ air horn blasting]

12:12.240 --> 12:13.413
[ laughing]

12:13.481 --> 12:14.826
Pretty annoying, huh, Leela?

12:14.895 --> 12:17.206
What? Are you talking?

12:17.274 --> 12:18.895
Oh, God, I'm deaf!

12:18.965 --> 12:21.274
Oops. I'm so, so sorry, Leela.

12:21.344 --> 12:23.447
I just wanted to annoy you.

12:23.517 --> 12:25.758
What? Oh, this is horrible!

12:25.826 --> 12:28.793
I won't be able
to hear Fry's opera!

12:28.861 --> 12:30.826
[ sobbing]

12:30.895 --> 12:33.413
Ah, how delightfully ironic.

12:33.481 --> 12:34.895
It's not ironic.

12:34.965 --> 12:36.172
It's just mean.

12:36.240 --> 12:37.620
Take this!

12:37.688 --> 12:38.895
[ air horn blast fizzles out]

12:38.965 --> 12:41.481
Ooh, out of aerosol.

12:41.551 --> 12:43.067
Also ironic.

12:43.136 --> 12:44.274
Oh, yeah?

12:44.344 --> 12:46.517
Well, bite my shiny metal...

12:46.586 --> 12:48.240
Oh, no!!!

12:48.309 --> 12:51.931
.

12:52.000 --> 12:58.758
.

12:58.826 --> 13:00.447
Nobody tell
Fry I'm deaf.

13:00.517 --> 13:02.861
If he found
out I couldn't
hear his opera

13:02.931 --> 13:04.102
it'd break
his heart.

13:04.172 --> 13:05.481
Okay, deaf-o.

13:05.551 --> 13:06.724
[ whirring]

13:06.793 --> 13:09.447
Courtesans and gentlefops

13:09.517 --> 13:12.274
I bid you welcome
to myopera.

13:12.344 --> 13:15.793
Let us cavort
like the Greeks of old.

13:15.861 --> 13:18.172
You know the ones
I mean.

13:18.240 --> 13:21.551
[ orchestra tuning up]

13:21.620 --> 13:22.688
[ baton tapping stand]

13:22.758 --> 13:24.447
[ audience gasping]

13:24.517 --> 13:25.586
[ applause and cheers]

13:25.654 --> 13:26.688
Yay, Fry.

13:26.758 --> 13:28.724
I watch TV with that guy.

13:31.895 --> 13:34.654
[ orchestra plays]

13:38.895 --> 13:42.102
[ wind instrument solo]

13:43.861 --> 13:46.895
♪ Who is this one-eyed
female baby Moses? ♪

13:46.965 --> 13:50.481
♪ With courage in her
female baby smile? ♪

13:50.551 --> 13:52.206
♪ A savior from the stars♪

13:52.274 --> 13:54.102
♪ Or something stranger still?♪

13:54.172 --> 13:59.379
♪ Or just a lonely,
filthy, starving child? ♪

13:59.447 --> 14:01.136
Amy, Fry's looking at me.

14:01.206 --> 14:03.206
What am I supposed
to be feeling?

14:04.620 --> 14:05.654
Ah!

14:09.517 --> 14:11.447
♪ Leela! ♪

14:11.517 --> 14:13.033
♪ Leela, Leela! ♪

14:13.102 --> 14:14.309
♪ Save him! ♪

14:14.379 --> 14:16.000
♪ Save Fry, save Fry! ♪

14:16.067 --> 14:19.481
♪ Godzilla will devour him ♪

14:19.551 --> 14:21.172
♪ As for me,
I must be off ♪

14:21.240 --> 14:23.654
♪ To have my doctor
check this cough ♪

14:23.724 --> 14:24.758
[ coughing]

14:24.826 --> 14:26.240
♪ Good-bye! ♪

14:28.206 --> 14:30.620
I don't recall
ever fighting Godzilla

14:30.688 --> 14:33.000
but that is so
what I would have done.

14:33.067 --> 14:34.688
Oh, it was
a lovely show.

14:34.758 --> 14:36.274
[ crowd chatting]

14:36.344 --> 14:37.654
[ laughing]

14:37.724 --> 14:40.102
One diet double
Martini, please.

14:40.172 --> 14:41.551
And for you, sir?

14:41.620 --> 14:43.447
I'll just have
a Shirley Hemphill.

14:43.517 --> 14:45.000
Extra, extra!

14:45.067 --> 14:48.033
World's greatest opera
only half over!

14:48.102 --> 14:49.240
Half over?

14:49.309 --> 14:50.620
Oh!

14:50.688 --> 14:52.344
I'd give anything
to hear the rest.

14:52.413 --> 14:53.620
Anything?

14:53.688 --> 14:54.826
[ gasps]

14:54.895 --> 14:56.000
[ glass breaking]

14:56.067 --> 14:57.000
Thank you, sir.

14:57.067 --> 14:58.379
Now, as I was saying...

14:58.447 --> 15:00.136
Anything?

15:00.206 --> 15:03.240
Because I can give you
newrobotic ears.

15:03.309 --> 15:04.517
What?

15:04.586 --> 15:05.724
You can give me new ears?

15:05.793 --> 15:07.447
Wait.

15:07.517 --> 15:09.481
What seemingly reasonable thing
do you want in return?

15:09.551 --> 15:11.931
Just your hands,
my dear.

15:12.000 --> 15:13.688
Whatever you said, forget it!

15:13.758 --> 15:14.931
All right, then.

15:15.000 --> 15:16.033
Just one hand.

15:16.102 --> 15:18.586
Just... my left hand?

15:18.654 --> 15:20.413
Um... uh...

15:20.481 --> 15:22.240
USHER:
Please take your
seats for Act Two.

15:22.309 --> 15:24.447
HEDONISMBOT:
But I'm not
done vomiting!

15:24.517 --> 15:25.688
[ airy laugh]

15:25.758 --> 15:27.931
Oh, Daddy, I love...

15:28.000 --> 15:29.102
I can't stand it!

15:29.172 --> 15:30.274
[ deep breath]

15:30.344 --> 15:32.517
Okay, you can have my hand.

15:32.586 --> 15:33.793
Wonderful!

15:33.861 --> 15:35.620
Just sign here.

15:35.688 --> 15:38.793
Calculon, old friend,
I'm afraid I need your ears.

15:38.861 --> 15:42.447
Well, I do owe
you for giving
me this unholy...

15:42.517 --> 15:45.826
acting talent!

15:48.965 --> 15:51.793
[ ethereal music plays]

15:51.861 --> 15:53.033
I can hear!

15:53.102 --> 15:55.102
I can hear
like a safecracker.

15:55.172 --> 15:57.517
Hey, aren't you going
to take my hand?

15:57.586 --> 16:00.136
In good time.
You go enjoy
the opera.

16:04.067 --> 16:06.413
[ music plays]

16:06.481 --> 16:09.895
♪ To win Leela's heart
with the holophonor's art ♪

16:09.965 --> 16:13.102
♪ I need hands
of transcendental quickness ♪

16:13.172 --> 16:15.172
♪ Well, I don't
see any danger ♪

16:15.240 --> 16:18.172
♪ In gambling
with a stranger ♪

16:18.240 --> 16:22.136
♪ For my head is of
a most amazing thickness. ♪

16:22.206 --> 16:23.654
Ooh!

16:23.724 --> 16:24.965
[ laughter]

16:25.033 --> 16:27.654
[ angry groan]

16:27.724 --> 16:29.000
♪ I'm stupid,
I'm stupid ♪

16:29.067 --> 16:31.000
♪ I'm stupider
than you ♪

16:31.067 --> 16:34.309
♪ I'm stupider than you
in every way! ♪

16:34.379 --> 16:36.447
Stupider?

16:36.517 --> 16:38.000
Bah!

16:38.067 --> 16:40.172
This opera is as lousy
as it is brilliant.

16:40.240 --> 16:41.517
[ groans][ pained grunt]

16:41.586 --> 16:42.931
[ gasping]

16:45.620 --> 16:47.000
[ whimpers]

16:47.067 --> 16:48.931
Your lyrics lack subtlety.

16:49.000 --> 16:50.447
You can't just

16:50.517 --> 16:52.586
have your characters announce
how they feel.

16:52.654 --> 16:54.620
That makes me feel angry.

16:54.688 --> 16:56.344
Look, what do
you want?

16:56.413 --> 16:59.000
♪ I want my hands back. ♪

16:59.067 --> 17:01.517
[ fiendish laughter]

17:01.586 --> 17:03.136
Never!

17:03.206 --> 17:04.448
♪ A deal's a deal ♪

17:04.517 --> 17:06.481
♪ Even with a dirty dealer ♪

17:06.550 --> 17:08.103
♪ Very well ♪

17:08.172 --> 17:11.689
♪ Then I'll take
what I want from Leela. ♪

17:11.758 --> 17:13.448
Whoa!

17:15.034 --> 17:17.275
♪ Leela has promised me
her hand ♪

17:17.344 --> 17:18.586
[ all gasping]

17:18.654 --> 17:22.862
♪ Fry, you do not understand! ♪

17:22.931 --> 17:24.964
♪ I should have revealed ♪

17:25.034 --> 17:26.931
♪ I'd been deafened by Bender ♪

17:27.000 --> 17:28.448
♪ The shame ♪

17:28.517 --> 17:30.067
♪ The shame! ♪

17:30.136 --> 17:32.034
♪ But I feared
you'd stop writing ♪

17:32.103 --> 17:34.067
♪ This musical splendor ♪

17:34.136 --> 17:38.205
♪ Deception's the curse
of my whimsical gender ♪

17:38.275 --> 17:41.550
♪ He gave me mechanical ears ♪

17:41.619 --> 17:44.758
♪ Effective,
though just a bit garish ♪

17:44.826 --> 17:48.034
♪ In return
without shedding a tear ♪

17:48.103 --> 17:51.448
♪ I agreed
that I'd give him my hand ♪

17:51.517 --> 17:53.378
♪ In marriage! ♪

17:53.448 --> 17:55.000
Huh?What?

17:55.067 --> 17:58.723
♪ You'll give me your hand
in marriage ♪

17:58.792 --> 18:00.413
♪ Is this really
happening ♪

18:00.481 --> 18:02.481
♪ Or just being staged? ♪

18:02.550 --> 18:03.792
♪ It can't be real ♪

18:03.862 --> 18:05.758
♪ Not if Leela
is engaged ♪

18:05.826 --> 18:07.448
♪ That isn't what I meant ♪

18:07.517 --> 18:09.205
♪ That isn't what I signed ♪

18:09.275 --> 18:11.205
♪ You should have
checked the wording ♪

18:11.275 --> 18:13.378
♪ In the fine... ♪

18:13.448 --> 18:15.172
♪ Print ♪

18:15.240 --> 18:17.517
"I'll give you my hand... "

18:17.586 --> 18:20.136
♪ In marriage! ♪

18:20.205 --> 18:22.586
♪ The use of words
expressing something other ♪

18:22.654 --> 18:25.103
♪ Than their literal intention ♪

18:25.172 --> 18:29.172
♪ Now that is irony ♪

18:29.240 --> 18:30.792
[ gasping and grunting]

18:30.862 --> 18:34.309
♪ I will marry her now
and confine her to Hell ♪

18:34.378 --> 18:35.481
♪ How droll! ♪

18:35.550 --> 18:36.723
♪ How droll! ♪

18:36.792 --> 18:38.344
[ grunts]

18:38.413 --> 18:41.619
♪ Where Styx is a river
and not just a band ♪

18:41.689 --> 18:43.309
♪ Though they'll play
our reception ♪

18:43.378 --> 18:45.448
♪ If all goes as planned ♪

18:45.517 --> 18:50.654
♪ Unless Fry--
you surrender myhands! ♪

18:50.723 --> 18:52.862
[ dramatic orchestral
crescendo]

18:52.931 --> 18:55.034
[ quiet string and
percussion solo]

18:55.103 --> 18:57.481
♪ Destiny has cheated me ♪

18:57.550 --> 19:00.413
♪ By forcing me
to decide upon ♪

19:00.481 --> 19:03.586
♪ The woman that I idolize ♪

19:03.654 --> 19:06.964
♪ Or the hands of an automaton ♪

19:07.034 --> 19:09.034
♪ Without these hands
I can't complete ♪

19:09.103 --> 19:11.619
♪ The opera
that was captivating her ♪

19:11.689 --> 19:14.517
♪ But if keep them,
and she marries him ♪

19:14.586 --> 19:19.103
♪ Then he probably won't
want me dating her. ♪

19:19.172 --> 19:20.862
[ applause and cheering]Arooo!

19:20.931 --> 19:22.067
Brave-o!

19:22.136 --> 19:23.723
En-core!

19:23.792 --> 19:27.413
♪ I can't believe
the devil is so unforgiving ♪

19:27.481 --> 19:31.895
♪ I can't believe
everybody's just ad-libbing. ♪

19:31.964 --> 19:33.172
Oh. Ugh.

19:33.240 --> 19:36.275
♪ By the power vested in me ♪

19:36.344 --> 19:38.586
♪ By the state
of New New York... ♪

19:38.654 --> 19:41.136
No! Stop!

19:41.205 --> 19:42.586
Take my hands

19:42.654 --> 19:47.723
♪ You evil... metal... dork! ♪

19:47.792 --> 19:49.448
[ sobbing]

19:49.517 --> 19:50.862
[ fiendish laughter]

19:50.931 --> 19:52.654
[ gasps]

19:53.931 --> 19:55.586
Surgery in an opera?

19:55.654 --> 19:57.103
How wonderfully decadent!

19:57.172 --> 19:59.723
And just as I was beginning
to lose interest.

19:59.792 --> 20:03.654
Jambi, the chocolate icing!

20:03.723 --> 20:04.895
Oh!

20:04.964 --> 20:06.723
Oh, my, yes!

20:06.792 --> 20:07.723
[ giggling]

20:07.792 --> 20:09.136
Ooh.

20:09.205 --> 20:10.758
My hands!

20:10.826 --> 20:13.448
My horrible human hands!

20:13.517 --> 20:14.723
[ gasps]

20:14.792 --> 20:16.413
And what did you do
to my nails?

20:16.481 --> 20:18.034
I cleaned them.

20:18.103 --> 20:19.792
Now, if you'll
excuse me, it's
my poker night

20:19.862 --> 20:21.067
and I feel lucky.

20:21.136 --> 20:22.275
[ giggling]

20:22.344 --> 20:23.758
So it's back
to Hell for me!

20:23.826 --> 20:25.000
Come on, Nixon.

20:25.067 --> 20:26.240
Huh?

20:28.309 --> 20:29.586
[ muttering]

20:29.654 --> 20:30.517
[ Robot Devil chuckling]

20:30.586 --> 20:33.413
Less reality,
more fantasy!

20:33.481 --> 20:35.517
Resume the opera!

20:35.586 --> 20:37.481
But I can't play anymore!

20:37.550 --> 20:38.792
Yes, you can!

20:38.862 --> 20:40.067
The beauty was
in your heart

20:40.136 --> 20:41.862
not your hands.

20:46.862 --> 20:52.240
[ plays discordant notes]

20:52.309 --> 20:54.172
[ booing]

20:54.240 --> 20:56.895
Your music's bad,
and you should feel bad.

20:56.964 --> 20:58.103
[ booing]

20:58.172 --> 20:59.103
[ grunting]

20:59.172 --> 21:00.689
Ah, ooh!

21:00.758 --> 21:02.000
Whoa. Aah! Hey!

21:02.067 --> 21:03.000
Whoa-oh!

21:04.723 --> 21:06.240
Extra, extra!

21:06.309 --> 21:09.136
Greatest opera
of all time sucks!

21:09.205 --> 21:11.378
I'll take eight.

21:18.309 --> 21:20.344
[ footsteps echoing]

21:20.413 --> 21:24.000
LEELA:
Please don't stop playing, Fry.

21:24.067 --> 21:26.792
I want to hear how it ends.

21:34.826 --> 21:38.103
[ playing simple melody]
